For more information about Twisted, including release notes, please see the [wiki:TwistedProject Twisted project page]. You can get older releases from our [http://tmrc.mit.edu/mirror/twisted/ download site].

(If you are looking for the older Twisted 1.3 release, see the [http://twistedmatrix.com/products/download old download page]. Twisted 1.3 is deprecated, but may still be required by some third-party applications.)

To checkout code from the repository, use:
  svn co svn://svn.twistedmatrix.com/svn/Twisted/trunk

= Documentation =

A good starting point is the [http://twistedmatrix.com/projects/core/documentation/howto/index.html core developer guide] ([http://twistedmatrix.com/projects/core/documentation/howto/book.pdf PDF]) and [http://twistedmatrix.com/documents/current/api/ API reference]. Sub-project documentation ([http://twistedmatrix.com/projects/conch/documentation/howto/index.html conch], etc.) is available from the appropriate [wiki:TwistedProjects project] pages. You can also purchase the book [http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0596100329/httpitamorg-20?creative=327641&camp=14573&link_code=as1 Twisted Network Programming Essentials] by Abe Fetting, published by O'Reilly.

